# Device Synchronization (P2P)

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph "Multi-Device Architecture"
        
        Device1[Device A - Laptop]
        Device2[Device B - Phone]
        Device3[Device C - Tablet]
        
        Device1 <-->|P2P Sync| Sync[Entanglement Protocol]
        Device2 <-->|P2P Sync| Sync
        Device3 <-->|P2P Sync| Sync
        
        Sync --> Encrypted[Encrypted Transit]
        Encrypted --> CRDT[CRDT Merge]
        CRDT --> Verify[Merkle Verification]
    end
    
    style Device1 fill:#e94560,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style Device2 fill:#3498db,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style Device3 fill:#27ae60,stroke:#333,color:#fff
```

## Sync Protocol

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Device A
    participant B as Device B
    
    A->>B: Hello + Device Identity
    B->>A: Hello + Device Identity
    
    A->>A: Compute Merkle root
    B->>B: Compute Merkle root
    
    A->>B: My root is X
    B->>A: My root is Y
    
    alt Roots match
        Note over A,B: Already in sync - no action
    else Roots differ
        A->>B: Send diff (encrypted)
        B->>A: Send diff (encrypted)
        
        A->>A: Merge CRDT
        B->>B: Merge CRDT
        
        A->>A: Verify new root
        B->>B: Verify new root
    end
    
    Note over A,B: Both roots now match
```

## CRDT Conflict Resolution

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph "Conflict Resolution Strategy"
        
        Add[G-Counter: ACU additions]
        Meta[LWW-Register: Metadata updates]
        
        subgraph "Merge Logic"
            Merge1[Union of ACU sets]
            Merge2[Vector clock comparison]
            Merge3[Last-writer-wins for conflicts]
        end
        
        Add --> Merge1
        Meta --> Merge2
        Merge2 --> Merge3
        
        Merge1 --> Result[Merged Vault]
        Merge3 --> Result
    end
    
    style Add fill:#e94560,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style Meta fill:#3498db,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style Result fill:#27ae60,stroke:#333,color:#fff
```